caption: It was a surprise for me to find a Church run by the Blessed Sacrament fathers here. The church is small but the ambience is conducive for prayers and meditation as it is quiet and less frequented by visitors. We left the church happy with our wishes and prayers offered before an contemporarily designed altar.
Attended mass in French (I am American and speak very little) but the parish was very welcoming and kind.
Tomb of Saint Pierre-Julien Eymard who published magnificent works entitled "The Divine Eucharist" which allow us to understand this sacrament and what Catholicism is
Very beautiful church. Magnificent piet√† painted by Delacroix.
In the afternoon during the week, I was able to go there to visit Christ: we could worship him there in deep spiritual calm. The chapel is very well maintained, it is clean, beautiful and fresh.

I experienced this church as very sober: Attendance was poor, people didn't genuflect in front of the celebration altar. Everything is very worn out, even in the house, partly dusty and the workers are not always well paid. The former student foyer is too big and too expensive; guest operations are no longer viable in the old building.
Very beautiful church where you can gather in peace
Small church with very few visitors! Damage . Great for those who want to meditate in silence....and a moving Saint Joseph
In this church of the Holy Sacrament I saw the recumbent figure of Saint Pierre Julien HEYMARD. He solved all problems by praying before the Tabernacle.
This place is calm We can see the body of St Julien Eymard there In a beautiful hunt
Very beautiful chapel to pray and meditate
